etween science, technology, and social change. The argument presented shifts the debate on topics such as the relationship between growth and sustainability, and thus has important policy implications. This book will be of great interest to scholars, scientists, and anyone interested in understanding how science and technology are transforming our world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Industries / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362645440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503626454423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503626454/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles